This paper deals with the design of a parallel algorithm for solving positive semidefinite programs. The algorithm is based on the work of Luby and Nisan [1993] for positive linear programs, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves the use of techniques from numerical analysis (cs.NA) and optimization (cs.DS), as well as the analysis of the algorithm's running time and approximation factor (cs.CC, cs.LG).
